726769f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 64th Street
726769f-a.text:
Gra-d Avenue (old numbers 108-114), north side, between
64th Street, and Remsen Place, showing the Long Island Houae
(peaked roof) which was the property of Louis Reitzel in 1873.
Grand Avenue at this point was Maspeth Avenue in 1873. John
Reitzel, a batchelor occupied thhe premises in 1934.
1922
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection
